           Job Description 
           
             Laboratory Technician 2  
 PURPOSE: To prepare samples for analysis in accordance with established protocols under direct supervision. Work on assignments that are moderately complex in nature where discretion is required in resolving problems and making routine recommendations. Under minimal direction, conduct qualified chemical and physical laboratory analyses to identify contaminants in hazardous waste, environmental, and industrial hygiene media. May make detailed observations, analyze data, and interpret results.   
   
   
 ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS:  
 Conducts simple, routine laboratory procedures, such as preparation of environmental samples for chemical analysis, reagents, and standard solutions.  
 Performs radioanalytical and wet chemistry procedures under direct supervision.  
 Performs data reduction under direct supervision using Microsoft Excel and Word.  
 Maintains laboratory equipment to ensure cleanliness and availability.  
 Performs routine quality control procedures for laboratory instrumentation, including balances, pipets, and pH meters.  
 Monitors laboratory periodically to check for radionuclide contamination. Monitors the routine quality control activities to ensure on time performance and conformance to established limits.    REQUIREMENTS:   Associate's degree in chemistry and two to four years job related experience required or an equivalent combination of related training and experience. Must have experience in wet chemical sample preparation and analyses to identify radiological and non-radiological contaminants in environmental and industrial media. Must have experience in using basic laboratory equipment, including analytical balances, pipets, pH meters, centrifuges, etc. Proficiency in Microsoft Excel and Word required.    
 
         
